# Hacking

This file lists important information for anyone working on developing this software.

## Constributions

### Every new Contributor

- should go in `AUTHORS`

## Changes

### Every Change

- should have a user story in `proj/`
- should be documented in `ChangeLog`
- should have an entry in `NEWS` if it's user facing
- should mention the user story number in the commit message

## Releases

### Every Release

- document in `ChangeLog`
- document in `NEWS`
- versioning should follow semantic versioning spec
- bump version number in `README`
- bump version number in `configure.ac`
- bump build number in `configure.ac`
- create a tag in the scm
 - `git tag -a v1.2.3 -m "Version 1.2.3 Build 42"`

### Release Cycle

- happens on the 1st and 15th of every month

## Major Design Features

### Minimal Dependencies

- no dependencies besides a standard C library.
- anything that needs a C library is in `src/sys.c`.

